  <body>
    <segment id="1">

Queen of hearts stings</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="26" relname="span">

An election result that satisfies both opponents -
</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="12" relname="interpretation"> 

that is a rarity!
</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="31" relname="span"> 

But yesterday evening both mayoral candidates were quite satisfied. 
</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="27" relname="span"> 

Elisabeth Herzog-von_der_Heide (SPD) was pleased with the election result, 
</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="2" relname="e-elaboration"> 

which brought her more than 60 percent , 
</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="28" relname="conjunction"> 

and Hans-Jürgen Akuloff (PDS) was pleased that he achieved the best result for the PDS so far.
</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="4" relname="concession">

This was of course all the easier as there was only one opposing candidate this time.
</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="29" relname="span">  

The party landscape in Luckenwalde is of course still broadly diversified.
</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="30" relname="span">  

Therefore neither SPD nor PDS supporters need to fly high now. 
</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="22" relname="span"> 

Yesterday&apos;s election result is the personal result of the two candidates
</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="6" relname="elaboration"> 

after they beat a third in the first round of voting.
</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="22" relname="interpretation"> 

Nothing more and nothing less.
</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="24" relname="span">

After the first round of “Skat”, Queen of Hearts then beat Duke in the second round of “Mau Mau”.
</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="21" relname="span">  

Not a surprising result, nor an incredibly outstanding one, but a clear run-off result.
</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="20" relname="span">  

The extreme tension was gone anyway,

</segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="19" relname="span"> 

as the first election had already decided the outcome,
</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="17" relname="e-elaboration"> 

which was now only confirmed by the run-off election.

</segment>
